{"type":"message","id":"391cf291","parentId":"c61f7975","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:51:04.993Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 11:51 GMT+2] GITHUB INTEGRATOR (Parallel Flash Stream).\n\n1.  **Objective:** Analyze the GitHub App `arkadiy-bot-manager` integration process for OpenClaw.\n    *   *Reference:* `docs_archive/github_documentation.json`.\n\n2.  **CLI Command Prep:**\n    *   What exact `openclaw` or `git` commands are needed to configure the app?\n    *   (Usually: `openclaw config set github.appId <id>`, or setting ENV vars).\n    *   Identify the exact 4 pieces of data needed from the user.\n\n3.  **Data Requirements List:**\n    *   Create a clear, copy-paste list for Bogdan.\n    *   Format: `Variable Name` (Where to find it on GitHub).\n\n4.  **Report:**\n    *   Ready-to-use CLI commands.\n    *   The \"Shopping List\" for App credentials."}],"timestamp":1771149064991}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7b289cc","parentId":"391cf291","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:51:06.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771149066074_189","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"docs_archive/github_documentation.json"},"thoughtSignature":"CiEBjz1rX2yfcjTJl2eLLnKfzzfzFxB2aRXMF+5NncLJE2E="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":4869,"output":15,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4884,"cost":{"input":0.0024345,"output":0.000045,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0024795}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771149064993}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0b37e36","parentId":"a7b289cc","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:51:06.247Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771149066074_189","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"app_name\": \"arkadiy-bot-manager\",\n  \"role\": \"The GitHub App acts as a dedicated identity for the bot within the GitHub ecosystem. Unlike Personal Access Tokens (PATs) which are tied to a specific user, a GitHub App is its own entity with fine-grained permissions.\",\n  \"requirements\": {\n    \"App ID\": \"Unique identifier for the GitHub App.\",\n    \"Installation ID\": \"Specific ID for the account/organization where the app is installed.\",\n    \"Private Key\": \".pem file used to sign JWTs for authentication.\",\n    \"Client Secret\": \"Used for server-to-server interactions (optional for basic bot operations).\"\n  },\n  \"benefits\": [\n    \"Higher rate limits: 5000 requests/hour (vs 60/hour for unauthenticated or basic PAT).\",\n    \"Fine-grained permissions: Only grant access to specific repositories and actions.\",\n    \"Check Run status reporting: Allows the bot to report build/test status directly on PRs.\",\n    \"Improved security: Credentials are tied to the app, not a human user account.\"\n  ]\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771149066245}}
